<TEXT>
an orange juice producttampering case 
widened wednesday when a suburban supermarket employee found a 
juice carton punctured with a syringe needle and bearing a note 
warning of poison the third such incident this week 
the latest carton was discovered at a hughes market in canoga 
park said police officer fred nixon the needle and juice were 
sent to a lab for testing but results werent expected for about 
three days he said 
the mo method was very similar to the mo in the two 
previous cases nixon said we dont know if we have a copycat 
or what 
as in the two earlier cases in nearby woodland hills a needle 
of the type that attaches to a hypodermic syringe was stuck into 
the twoquart cardboard carton and a note suggested poison had been 
injected nixon said he described the note as a warning but 
refused to reveal its exact wording 
tests as yet incomplete tentatively cleared one of the first 
two cartons of contamination and no one drank from any of the 
cartons 
the juice brand tampered with wednesday was citrus hill in the 
two previous cases monday at a vons market and tuesday at an alpha 
beta market the brand was minute maid all three cartons were 
found outside the refrigerator cases where they are stocked and 
none of the needles in the cartons had syringes attached nixon 
said 
on wednesday hughes pulled all chilled orange juice from the 
shelves of the store where the tampering took place awaiting a 
fresh shipment said harland polk vice president for sales he 
said workers had been ordered to watch for tampering after the 
first incident 
police urged shoppers who had recently bought orange juice from 
that store to return it and they suggested inspecting juice 
cartons before buying them at any store in the area in the western 
end of the san fernando valley suburbs 25 miles northwest of 
downtown los angeles 
officials at the two stores involved in the earlier cases and at 
minute maid said they knew of no labor troubles or personal grudges 
that might have prompted the tampering and nixon said the entry of 
a second brand might discount that theory 
the note on the carton in alpha beta referred to unsafe 
packaging said store spokesman bill wade 
