<TEXT>
edwin meese iii the conservative attorney 
general with a lawandorder philosophy was a magnet for 
controversy virtually from the time he set foot in the nations 
capital but he never lost the confidence of the boss president 
reagan 
for nearly 20 years meeses life has been entwined with 
reagans career as the republican governor of california and then 
as president since reagan was elected to the white house in 1981 
meese has been at the center of power first serving as counselor 
to the president before his confirmation as attorney general in 
1985 
he is a good friend reagan said tuesday shortly after 
meese announced he planned to resign in the summer to pursue other 
opportunities 
a native of oakland calif meese helped reopen debate on 
longsettled issues which are at the heart of the liberal agenda 
from affirmative action and school busing to the rights of the 
accused 
his outspoken embrace of the conservative agenda his dogged 
determination to hang onto his job his attacks on the supreme 
court and his personal conduct seemed to attract criticism from all 
sides even from republicans 
through it all meese 56 a stocky lawyer and a police buff 
kept his composure played down his problems and seemed to enjoy 
sparring with his critics 
what is wrong with being affable meese once asked a 
colleague 
after a grueling 13month confirmation hearing to attain the 
attorney generals post meese said i am not bitter at all 
before his nomination an independent counsel had investigated 
meeses role in obtaining government jobs for financial 
benefactors the report cleared meese of any wrongdoing 
at the justice department meeses tenure was marked by turmoil 
a major problem began in late in 1986 when us attorney general 
rudolph giuliani launched a probe of wedtech corp whose 
executives allegedly doled out payoffs to influence public 
officials to assist the south bronx ny defense contractor 
by april 1987 longtime meese friend e robert wallach who got 
13 million from the company was at the center of the probe the 
next month independent counsel james mckay began examining meeses 
record of assistance to wedtech which occurred at wallachs behest 
mckays report which has not been made public was filed 
tuesday in federal court it apparently absolves meese of any 
criminal misconduct 
during mckays investigation meese clung to his post despite 
protest resignations from two of his top aides and a growing chorus 
of calls from a number of conservative congressmen for him to quit 
meese had the support of the only politician who mattered reagan 
meeses legal troubles were the final phase in the political 
life of a man who has had the highest public profile of any 
attorney general since robert kennedy 
as the nations chief law enforcement officer meese opened fire 
on the supreme court accusing the justices of weakening the 
constitution with ad hoc and bizarre rulings he said the 
decisions were not the supreme law of the land 
among other things meese said the court had gone astray by 
applying the bill of rights to the states which has led to 
legalizing abortion and insistence by the court that government and 
religion not mix 
the attorney general also attacked the miranda warning governing 
pretrial police interrogation procedures saying it only helps 
guilty defendants 
one of meeses legacies is the federal judiciary since he 
became attorney general meese has played a pivotal role is 
selecting about 200 judicial appointees 
in california meese was executive assistant and chief of staff 
to thengov reagan from 1969 through 1974 he was the governors 
legal affairs secretary for two years before that 
before joining reagans staff in sacramento meese was a deputy 
district attorney in alameda county calif in that job he 
advocated a tough response to student demonstrators opposing the 
vietnam war 
prior to reagans election as president meese was a professor 
at the university of san diego law school specializing in criminal 
justice 
meese also had his share of personal troubles in washington in 
1982 his 19yearold son scott was killed in an automobile 
crash his wife ursula held a series of jobs most recently 
serving as a 40000ayear official with the multiple sclerosis 
society the couple has a daughter dana and a son michael 
