here is a transcript of attorney 
general edwin meese iiis news conference tuesday 
i have a statement to make and then ill be glad to answer any 
questions 
the independent counsel today filed his statutory report after 
an investigation that has lasted approximately 14 months and has 
gone into many subjects heard dozens of witnesses and scrutinized 
thousands of documents including all of my personal financial 
records since 1981 
the filing of the report by the independent counsel in line 
with his previously stated finding confirms that after an 
exhaustive investigation he has determined that there is no basis 
for criminal proceedings with respect to any of the matters that he 
has examined 
i am gratified by this result but not surprised 
i knew from the beginning of this investigation that my conduct 
has been at all times lawful and that if the truth were told 
there would be no grounds for any criminal action 
this past year has been enormously difficult for my family and 
me 
we have been subjected to a barrage of unfair misleading and 
false information circulated through the media 
i answered any and all questions that the independent counsel 
put to me in grand jury sessions and through depositions throughout 
the year 
but i have not yet been able to publicly confront the misleading 
and false allegations because of the ongoing independent counsels 
investigation 
now that the report has been filed however i will begin to 
present a full public response 
my attorneys and i will study the independent counsels report 
which we have not yet received but which we hope to receive today 
or tomorrow and we will prepare an appropriate and timely reply 
as the law provides 
when the court determines what portion if any of the report 
should be made public i trust that my written response will 
accompany that publication 
i will then make myself available to answer any and all 
questions 
i look forward to that opportunity because i am confident that 
when the public is able to hear both sides of the story not just 
the prosecutors view presented by the independent counsel it 
will be clear to all that i have acted lawfully and properly 
now that the independent counsel has finished his task and one 
of the most exhaustive thorough and costly investigations of any 
public official has been completed the false allegations have been 
put to rest it is therefore an appropriate time for me to announce 
certain decisions with respect to my personal future 
over the past two months i have indicated publicly that when i 
have achieved several objectives in the department of justice and 
have set the record straight and when it is in the interest of my 
family and myself that i return to private life i would leave the 
post of attorney general 
i have stated that i would not resign under a cloud or until i 
was completely vindicated 
i have refused to bend to the constant drumbeat of political and 
media pressure because i have a responsibility to uphold which 
involves an important principle not only for myself and this 
administration but for future government officials who are 
subjected to untrue allegations 
as i have said before to allow myself to be hounded out of 
office by false accusations or allegations unjust political 
attacks and media clamor would undermine the integrity of our 
system and would abandon the principles of justice which i have 
championed throughout my life 
</TEXT>
