<TEXT>
the us navys downing of iran air flight 
655 will likely fuel debate on a proposed un naval peacekeeping 
force the soviets are pushing as a way to diminish washingtons 
presence in the persian gulf 
the attack sunday on the airliner with 290 people aboard will 
also complicate un efforts to mediate between iran and iraq and 
bring about a ceasefire in their 7yearold conflict 
last september in his annual report un secretarygeneral 
javier perez de cuellar called for new innovative forms of 
peacekeeping perhaps including a un naval force to protect 
civilian shipping and maintain maritime peace 
but washington which has deployed the navy in the gulf to 
assert its strategic interests and protect neutral commercial 
shipping has said it is not leaving the oilrich strategic 
waterway 
still the us naval presence in the gulf is increasingly 
controversial and sundays jetliner downing during the latest in 
a series of usiranian clashes demonstrates the volatility of 
the region and the problems us forces face in trying to keep the 
peace 
the soviet union its allies iran and other nations argue that 
far from keeping the peace the us presence inflames tensions 
in commenting on the disaster the official soviet press agency 
tass said the tragedy has borne out once again that the united 
states naval fleet must leave the persian gulf without delay 
the pentagon said the us warship that shot down the iran air 
airbus mistook it for an iranian f14 jet fighter 
iran has requested a security council meeting that is expected 
early next week and would likely see the soviets press their call 
for withdrawal of all us military forces from the gulf and 
introducing an international naval force under un command 
the councils five permanent members are the united states the 
soviet union britain china and france 
the two superpowers have not participated in other un 
peacekeeping operations because they were perceived as putting 
their national strategic interests first the soviet union now 
wants to change that 
since last september soviet foreign minister eduard a 
shevardnadze has been saying that the time has come for a un 
naval peacekeeping force 
under the principles of un peacekeeping such a force can only 
operate with the consent of the parties concerned 
it must be impartial and not favor either side and it must not 
use force except as a last resort and only in selfdefense 
but the united nations and its peacekeeping forces are facing a 
financial crisis and the prospects of funding a new naval force are 
bleak and compounded by us resistance 
the attack sunday will also hurt efforts to end the iraniraq 
war 
un officials and diplomats say the attack on the airbus has 
generated sympathy for iran and hardened irans determination not 
to stop fighting until iraq is branded the aggressor 
that demand has been a major roadblock in getting iran to accept 
a ceasefire in the bloody conflict 
</TEXT>
