the government promised to make wednesdays 
general elections free of violence and fraud and opposition 
parties mobilized thousands of pollwatchers nationwide to hold the 
government to its word 
the final tally wasnt expected before the end of the week but 
the outcome is virtually certain the governing institutional 
revolutionary party hasnt lost a presidential election since its 
founding in 1929 
voters will choose a new president and members of congress at 
55000 polling places across the country under guard by thousands 
of troops 
polling stations open at 8 am 10 am edt and counting is to 
begin when they close 10 hours later many parties plan to begin 
releasing unofficial results on election night 
