survivors standing to demand compensation is tenuous at best 
the problem for the survivors is that the us government is 
protected by sovereign immunity from claims by foreigners although 
there are exceptions to that such as claims under the federal 
tort claims act they would appear to be ruled out in the iranian 
case because the accident occurred during combat 
its not simple negligence said lowenfeld the tort claims 
