varazdin about 30 miles north of zagreb also were on strike 
they marched on the towns streets today chanting we want 
bread and work and demanded that the factory temporarily closed 
for producing losses be reopened 
yugoslavia registered an alltime record of 1600 strikes last 
year involving more than 300000 workers but most of those work 
stoppages were staged inside factory gates 
