<TEXT>
the states highest court has ruled 
west virginias gun law unconstitutional which some authorities 
say means people may legally carry concealed weapons 
the state supreme court ruling effectively invalidated 
prohibition against carrying dangerous and deadly weapons state 
police superintendent wf donohoe said tuesday 
however all other firearmsrelated charges are still valid 
such as brandishing assault with a deadly weapon etc he said 
a department of public safety spokesman said authorities are 
worried about an increase in gunrelated crimes 
absolutely people are carrying weapons indiscriminately 
people are going to be shot with tempers flying there are going to 
be increases in assaults with police officers increases in deaths 
in domestic situations said trooper ric robinson 
it in general puts everyone in a far more dangerous posture 
the court unanimously ruled friday that a 1986 state 
constitutional amendment invalidated a 1975 law requiring permits 
for people carrying concealed weapons 
the amendment overwhelmingly passed by voters guarantees that 
a person has the right to keep and bear arms for the defense of 
self family home and state and for lawful hunting and 
recreational use 
supporters including the national rifle association said it 
simply reinforced existing rights and was not a threat to state gun 
laws 
donohoe said the ruling leaves some areas unclear 
it is still an unanswered question as to whether the law is 
still enforceable against nonfirearm dangerous and deadly weapons 
such as dirks bowieknives and billy clubs he said 
the supreme court ruling stemmed from the 1987 arrest of a man 
on drunken driving charges when princeton police tried to charge 
him with carrying a concealed weapon magistrate harold l buckner 
cited the constitutional amendment and refused to issue the warrant 
a circuit judge upheld buckner and the state supreme court 
agreed justices also ruled that the legislature can issue new gun 
control laws which would stand up under the ruling 
senate judiciary chairman larry tucker a democrat says he 
thinks police can handle the situation until next regular session 
in january the state already has had three special sessions this 
year and it would be a waste of money to come back again said 
tucker 
under the stricken law west virginians were allowed to carry 
firearms without permits only to and from a place of purchase or 
repair an authorized shooting range or during hunting seasons 
violation meant a mandatory sixmonth jail sentence for first 
offenders a second offense was a felony 
robinson said those constraints are gone if you want to take 
a pistol and stick it in your pocket your purse your swim trunks 
the supreme court decision allows that 
but he said he did not think most west virginians now were 
packing guns id say most people are not aware of the 
decision he said 
