cannot discuss this issue since it is a legal matter she said 
brauer said the doctors gave the dilantin in the course of 
treating the women shortly before their babies were delivered and 
not as an experiment 
he contended that informed written consent was obtained from 
every patient treated while hospital officials have contended that 
many patients were given the drug without their knowledge or 
consent 
the doctors who face a disciplinary hearing july 18 
administered the anticonvulsants for four months beginning last 
september after receiving approval from the hospitals medical 
staff for a study involving 50 women undergoing emergency caesarean 
section 
