a soviet research balloon exploded 
off jutlands east coast wednesday dropping a parachute with 
unknown equipment into the sea the defense command said 
the equipment hit the sea about 830 pm more than an hour 
after it was dropped from the balloon maj mogens meyerpedersen 
told the associated press he said the balloon exploded by a 
selfdestructive device 
the balloon at a height of 112000 feet was programmed to drop 
its equipment northeast of moscow but a faulty rudder moved it off 
course to the west it drifted over southern sweden before 
exploding over djursland in northeast jutland 
a crew from the defense command headed for the scene by boat to 
retrieve the container with the parachuted equipment 
soviet authorities told the foreign ministry about the errant 
balloon wednesday morning they would not say what kind of 
equipment it carried 
the balloon 198 feet in diameter had a volume of 6300000 
cubic feet it weighed 1584 pounds and carried 264 pounds of 
equipment the soviets said 
danish television reported earlier the government had not yet 
decided whether the equipment would be returned 
the soviet news agency novosti said the balloon was launched 
june 28 as part of a series of atmospheric experiments 
