<TEXT>
a panamanianregistered ship seized on the high 
seas with more than 72 tons of marijuana was towed into port 
wednesday and the coast guard said its capture was the largest 
drug bust ever on the west coast 
officials said the encounter bay had endured 60 rounds of 
machinegun fire about 600 miles offshore last friday and 
surrendered only when threatened with cannon fire 
the ship was towed into port under tight security by the coast 
guard cutter boutwell which was flying a makeshift pot buster 
flag 
the crew of 18 including three americans one from england 
one from new zealand and 13 from indonesia thailand and singapore 
were photographed and fingerprinted aboard the boutwell in 
preparation for an appearance before a us magistrate 
