commandant used the occasion to criticize funding cuts in the 
coast guards patrol budget he said the bust was the largest ever 
on the west coast 
this ought to indicate to people that its a flourishing 
business and for the government not to give the coast guard proper 
funds to interdict is foolhardy said kramek 
agents from the us drug enforcement administration were 
waiting on shore for the converted oilrig supply ship and set up 
security for the crew and for the cargo which will be burned 
officials said 
