<TEXT>
three survivors of nazi camps 
testified wednesday in the deportation case of josef schwammberger 
that the former nazi ss captain personally shot jews to death 
almost daily most with a pistol 
schwammberger 76 has been accused of killing at least 5000 
jews as commandant of the rozwadow and przemysl labor camps for 
jews in nazioccupied poland during world war ii 
he escaped austria with the help of the nazi odessa network in 
1948 and made his way to argentina in 1949 where he was arrested 
last november 
the survivors abraham secemski of chicago edward blonder of 
miami and morris reiter of toronto testified before the 
government for two days regarding their experiences in camps 
commanded by schwammberger in 194243 said their lawyer martin 
mendelsohn 
they said that besides killing jews with his own hand 
schwammberger starved prisoners killed those who were sick or 
became unable to work and for fun set an attack dog on jewish 
prisoners 
he was a sadist an evil person he played games of life with 
humans with jews said blonder 67 who was in six different war 
camps including przemysl with schwammberger he always called us 
dogs schweinhund 
he was the god the judge the jury the executioner he was 
everything said secemski who was in rozwadow his uncle was 
shot to death by schwammberger said secemski 
secemski lost 97 family members during the war only he and one 
brother survived 
reiter 57 who met secemski in przemysl said he came to 
argentina for the humanity of the world and to show that after 
40 years people cannot hide from the crimes theyve done 
mendelsohn the washingtonbased legal counsel for the simon 
