<TEXT>
late at night after most people have turned off the lights and 
gone to bed the party is just beginning on telephone lines across 
the country where the lonely make friends and the wimp becomes 
macho 
hi this is baby boy looking for baby girl said one 
latenight caller on a party line serving washington dc and the 
nearby maryland suburbs 
baby girl apparently wasnt at that party but it was hard to 
tell with the chaotic jumble of voices and occasional bursts of 
obscenities and sexual directions on the line 
i want you new york another male caller said during a 
moment of calm 
i want you too a woman answered 
party lines like this one can take the loneliness out of living 
for many at least those willing to pay as much as 2 per minute of 
anonymous conversation 
among an estimated 400 talk services nationwide are dating lines 
for adult singles and gays lines for teenagers lines for 
discussions about politics and sports even lines where callers can 
exchange trivia or pick up a joke to tell the next day at the 
office 
i just like making new friends said john explaining why he 
has become a regular on one of the 20 or so party lines available 
to district of columbia callers 
like many others john calls nearly every night to see whats 
happening and occasionally to find a date 
its a very popular service said betsy superfon vice 
president of seattlebased omnicall one of the largest party line 
operators in the country people are lonely and want to reach out 
and talk to people its somebody to talk to who isnt charging 
you to sit on his couch 
it can also be a fantasy land of illusion 
you can be anything you want on the telephone she said 
sometimes it seems every girl is blonde with blue eyes and is 
going to be a doctor and every man has dark hair green eyes and 
drives a porsche 
about half the callers dial in just to listen and most of the 
others call just to talk anonymously superfon said but officials 
at other lines estimate that as many as 60 percent of callers want 
to meet their newfound friends in person 
we have people finding jobs weve had a couple of marriages 
and countless close friends said jim day marketing director 
for baltimorebased jaali inc for people who are lonely or new 
in town its a unique way to meet its an opportunity for minds 
to meet before finding out the belt size 
the idea for gab lines started in brazil when local businessman 
luiz carlos bravo noticed that when phone lines for his recorded 
dialajoke service got crossed inadvertently turning the 
service into a party line the volume of calls went up 
people enjoyed talking to each other he said they didnt 
care about the jokes 
the idea spread to england and then the united states 
party lines now operate in 24 states and the district of 
columbia though no chat lines operate in new jersey and delaware 
callers in those states can reach lines in pennsylvania and new 
york 
these lines produced an estimated 90 million for phone 
companies and vendors last year according to the information 
industry bulletin an industry newsletter 
not everyone is high on these gab lines though state public 
utility commissions and telephone companies say by far the most 
complaints come from parents whose children have run up huge bills 
on the lines phone companies usually forgive the charges for 
firsttime complainers and most offer blocking to prevent use of a 
phone for such calls also some states limit the price party lines 
can charge keeping rates as low as 10 cents a minute in some areas 
kids get on these lines and talk for hours said philip 
diehl director of telephone regulation for the texas public 
utility commission 
texas and southwestern bell had tried to prohibit live 
conversation on dialit lines but companies challenged the ban 
as an infringement of their free speech rights and prevented the 
phone company from cutting them off 
in california pacific bell also is locked in a battle to pull 
the plug on party lines 
we think that if chat lines are to exist they need to have 
some special safeguards to ensure that consumers are protected 
said pacific bell spokeswoman sandy hale 
pacific bell tried to run a talk line a few years ago but 
there were too many problems hale said despite monitors on the 
lines the talk often turned sexually explicit and callers violated 
the rule on anonymity by giving out names addresses and phone 
numbers 
many talkline companies say they have monitors on their lines 
to make sure the conversations remain anonymous but that rule is 
often broken on most services callers can request to be moved to 
a private line where such information can be exchanged without 
announcing it to others on the party line 
the monitors are also supposed to keep conversations clean and 
cut off abusive callers but claudia dulude president of the ixl 
group a denverbased market research firm in the dialit industry 
believes that even with monitors its virtually impossible to rid 
chat lines of sexual talk 
i tried running a clean talk line as part of her research 
and i couldnt do it im a professor at the university of 
colorado a harvard business school graduate and a mother of two i 
tried to do it but i couldnt she said 
the aids scare has made gay dating lines among the most 
successful talk lines with high volume and fewer bad debt problems 
than other lines she said 
many big cities are becoming saturated with talk lines new york 
telephone has about 20 lines in the new york metropolitan area 
applications pending for twice that many and more are coming in 
every day said spokesman steven marcus 
but some are leaving too phone medium inc of mill valley 
calif which has whittled down its inventory of party lines to 
two has made a business decision to phase out the live 
services said spokesman bob stevenson 
they are somewhat more prone to abuse by the customer than 
recorded programs weve had some difficulty with 
conversations on the line and people unwilling to pay for them 
for companies dulude said entry to the market is easy and 
relatively inexpensive about 5000 will buy the necessary 
equipment and a phone line 
but easy entry and saturated markets combined with complaints 
and bad debt mean a short lifespan for companies in the industry 
she believes 
i think theyre absolutely a fad she said politically 
theyll go out of favor as their revenue decreases the phone 
companies will say its not worth it to them 
