production and distribution of programs on both sides of the 
atlantic but that both production operations would remain 
independent 
responding to questions about possible changes in programming 
that produced the sometimes controversial st elsewhere arthur 
price mtms chief executive officer said there are going to be 
no changes in the creative attitude the company has displayed 
in a deal that must be approved by the tvs board of directors 
and various regulatory bodies the british firm agreed to pay 
2423 million cash for the privately held mtm 
additionally tvs will issue new stock it valued at 358 
million to four members of mtm management price miss moore who 
is a director mel blumenthal senior executive vice president and 
tom palmieri executive vice president that stock would give the 
four a combined 20 percent of tvs but miss moores 64 percent 
share and blumenthals 36 percent share wouldnt change hands 
until 1993 under the agreement 
blumenthal and price will get seats on the tvs board 
