ford motor co announced wednesday it is 
recalling about 60000 vans and extending the warranties on an 
additional 266000 because of possible wiring brake and 
transmission problems 
ford said it is recalling 60000 198688 model aerostar vans and 
wagons equipped with an optional trailer tow package for a wiring 
modification 
faulty wiring on the vehicles could overheat and cause a fire 
the automaker said to correct the problem dealers will install an 
additional fuse to protect the wiring 
ford said it is extending warranty coverage on a total of 
266028 aerostar vans built on or prior to march 3 1987 including 
the 60000 with wiring problems to correct a nonsafety related 
brake problem 
the front brakes on the affected vehicles make an annoying 
groaning noise ford said dealers will cover the cost of 
correcting the problem the automaker said ford said the noise 
does not affect the performance of the brakes 
also 136000 aerostars may have problems with their automatic 
transmissions as well as noisy brakes ford said 
transmissions on those vehicles may show premature clutch wear 
preventing the vans from shifting into reverse or third gear ford 
said adding that in some cases the problem could render the 
vehicle inoperable 
owners of the affected vans will have their warranty coverage 
extended to five years or 50000 miles for automatic transmissions 
the automaker also announced the recall of 516 1987 and 1988 
cf6000 cf7000 and cf8000 cargo trucks because of problems with 
the steering mechanism continued use could cause the steering gear 
to seize during lowspeed vehicle turning maneuvers 
there have been no reported injuries or accidents because of the 
problem ford said 
ford said it would notify vehicle owners of the recall by mail 
