payments of nearly 790 million with aetna of hartford conn and 
numerous other carriers company officials said 
manvilles reorganization plan requires insurance funding of 
615 million for a trust for compensating asbestos disease 
sufferers 
insurance proceeds in excess of the 615 million will pass 
through to the asbestos property damage trust which was created to 
handle property damage claims against manville 
richard b von wald manville senior vice president and general 
counsel said that under manvilles plan of reorganization the 
latest settlement ultimately would benefit the asbestos property 
damage trust 
